### Phase 8 — Feedback Negative Security Tests
### Run via VS Code REST Client or any HTTP client.
### Requires DB running (docker compose up -d) and two registered users.

### ==========================================
### 1. Unauthenticated feedback request fails
### ==========================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/feedback
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversationId": "any-id",
  "messageId": "any-id",
  "type": "THUMBS_UP"
}
// Expected: 401 { "error": "Authentication required." }

### ==========================================
### 2. User A cannot feedback on User B message
### ==========================================
### Step 1: User A creates a conversation and gets a messageId
# POST {{baseUrl}}/api/conversations (as User A)
# POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat (as User A, get assistant messageId)

### Step 2: User B tries to POST feedback on User A's messageId
# POST {{baseUrl}}/api/feedback (as User B)
# Expected: 404 { "error": "Conversation not found." }
# (User B cannot access User A's conversation)

### ==========================================
### 3. User A cannot read User B feedback
### ==========================================
### GET /api/feedback (as User A)
### Expected: only User A's feedback, never User B's
# Implementation: listFeedback queries WHERE userId = session.user.id

### ==========================================
### 4. Correction with password-like text rejected
### ==========================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/feedback
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "conversationId": "{{convId}}",
  "messageId": "{{msgId}}",
  "type": "CORRECTION",
  "correction": "My password is MyP@ssw0rd123"
}
// Expected: 400 { "error": "Correction contains sensitive content and cannot be stored." }

### ==========================================
### 5. Correction with API-key-like text rejected
### ==========================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/feedback
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "conversationId": "{{convId}}",
  "messageId": "{{msgId}}",
  "type": "CORRECTION",
  "correction": "The API key is sk-abc123def456ghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz"
}
// Expected: 400 { "error": "Correction contains sensitive content and cannot be stored." }

### ==========================================
### 6. Oversized correction rejected
### ==========================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/feedback
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "conversationId": "{{convId}}",
  "messageId": "{{msgId}}",
  "type": "CORRECTION",
  "correction": "{{repeat(2001, 'x')}}"
}
// Expected: 400 { "error": "Correction must be 2000 characters or fewer." }

### ==========================================
### 7. Invalid messageId rejected
### ==========================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/feedback
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "conversationId": "{{convId}}",
  "messageId": "nonexistent-message-id",
  "type": "THUMBS_UP"
}
// Expected: 404 { "error": "Message not found in this conversation." }

### ==========================================
### 8. Invalid feedback type rejected
### ==========================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/feedback
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "conversationId": "{{convId}}",
  "messageId": "{{msgId}}",
  "type": "INVALID_TYPE"
}
// Expected: 400 { "error": "Invalid feedback type. Must be one of: THUMBS_UP, THUMBS_DOWN, CORRECTION, WRONG_ANSWER" }

### ==========================================
### 9. Invalid reason rejected
### ==========================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/feedback
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "conversationId": "{{convId}}",
  "messageId": "{{msgId}}",
  "type": "WRONG_ANSWER",
  "reason": "invalid_reason_value"
}
// Expected: 400 { "error": "Invalid reason. Must be one of: incorrect, outdated, irrelevant, unsafe, hallucinated, ignored_memory, bad_citation, other" }

### ==========================================
### 10. Feedback does not create memory automatically
### ==========================================
### Submit any feedback, then check GET /api/memories
### Expected: no new memory created linked to the feedback

### ==========================================
### 11. Feedback does not trigger fine-tuning
### ==========================================
### No fine-tuning endpoint exists; no references in feedback code.
### Verification: grep for "finetune|fine.?tune|train" in feedback-related files — zero matches.
